FBIS4-58539 "drnes087_r_94004" FBIS-NES-94-087 Daily Report 5 May 1994 SOUTH ASIA India Spokesman Welcomes PLO-Israeli Accord on Self-Rule Spokesman Welcomes PLO-Israeli Accord on Self-Rule BK0505055494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 5 May 94 BK0505055494 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] India and several other countries have welcomed the signing of the historic agreement on Palestinian self-rule. An External Affairs Ministry spokesman said in New Delhi that India has given consistent support to the Palestinians in the peace process. He recalled that India is one of the few countries outside the region invited to witness the signing ceremony at Cairo. The Indian delegation led by the minister of state for external affairs, Mr. R.L. Bhatia, was present when the PLO chairman, Mr Yasir 'Arafat and the Israeli prime minister, Mr. Rabin, signed the landmark agreement.
